While lawsuits are very rarely used in divorce proceedings in San Marino it is still possible for a very aggressive person to use the courts to get their way. If people are acting in bad faith an attorney can take advantage of a secretly unfavorable fact hidden by the other party an make a much stronger case.

If an attorney is caught hiding facts they can be held criminally or civilly liable for serious breaches of ethics. Occasionally the courts offer lawyers to each side to make the process more affordable for the individual, unlike the United States a divorce court proceeding in San Marino will not drain your bank account dry.
